  <doc for="DataGridParentRowsLabelStyle">
    <summary>
      <para>Specifies how the parent row labels of a <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.DataGrid" />
control are displayed.</para>
    </summary>
    <remarks>
      <para>Use the members of this enumeration to set the value of
      the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.DataGrid.ParentRowsLabelStyle" /> property.</para>
      <para>Parent rows can be displayed only if the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.DataGrid" />
contains at least one <see cref="System.Data.DataRelation" /> to a second <see cref="System.Data.DataTable" />, and if the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.DataGrid.AllowNavigation" /> property is set to a value that allows navigation.</para>
    </remarks>
